          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "1"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "All of my life’s been filled with woes,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Trials beyond what most could bear;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Though of my suff’rings no one knows,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Yet of my staunchness I’m aware;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I think self’s been discarded, yet"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "What I’ve been through, I don’t forget!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I have received much grace, I know;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "No one on earth more so than I!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Upon my body, in my soul,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Evidence of God’s work I find."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I know all He has done in me,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Appreciate it thoroughly!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "3"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "All my success I clearly see,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And know my every righteous deed;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Pride enters in, unconsciously;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "My center shifts from God to me;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Yesterday’s manna I hold tight,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But it’s gone rotten overnight."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "4"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "When friends console me in my plight,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "When they express their sympathy,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I can no more conceal my pride,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Patience runs out immediately;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I fail as any common folks:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Cursing my birth, I’m thus exposed."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "5"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "O God, about Thee, much I’ve heard,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And can expound on Thee at length,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Yet my poor self’s corrupt, impure;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Never have I for Thee been changed;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I use Thy gifts to pride inflate,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Self even more to elevate."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "6"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But now mine eye has seen Thee, Lord;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Thy holiness — my filth’s exposed."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Thy shining light — I am destroyed,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Thy glory — deep contrition flows;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I hate myself; How could I be"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "With self obsessed so utterly?"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "7"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Oh, how ashamed, ashamed am I!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Self I adorned with Thy free grace!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I used Thy works to lift self high;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "My every motive’s low and base;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "My failure’s beyond salvaging;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "More shameful yet, my victory."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "8"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "What shame, that I so proud can be!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "What blindness, and what foolishness!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Filthiness to consider clean,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Or flesh consider beauteous."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Self-righteous I, obtuse as well,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Thy glory stealing for my self."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "9"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "That I’m corrupt, Thou knowest well;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "As for myself, I had no clue;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I thought I could rely on self,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But it is shameful, through and through;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "O Lord, today, please rescue me!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Come loose my bonds, and set me free!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "10"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "O Lord, my heart doth Thee implore:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Grant me some dust in which to lie;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Ashes to on my body pour,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "For fallen self repent thereby;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I am ashamed unceasingly,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "That so corrupt my heart could be."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "11"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "My words are so inaccurate;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "My life is shallow to the core;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "My every motive is corrupt,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And all my being I abhor."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I hate myself now, O my Lord;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "My only hope: abide in Thee."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "12"
    }
  ],
